Package: grass
Version: 5.0.0 
Revision: 1
GCC: 3.1
Maintainer: Matt Stephenson <cattrap@users.sourceforge.net>
Depends: gdal, atlas, postgresql (>= 7.2.2-1), libgl, libjpeg-shlibs, libpng-shlibs, libtiff-shlibs, fftw-shlibs, tcltk, unixodbc-nox-shlibs | unixodbc-shlibs (>= 2.2.1-15), gd-shlibs
BuildDepends: libjpeg, libpng, libtiff, fftw, readline (>= 4.3-5), tcltk-dev, unixodbc-nox | unixodbc (>= 2.2.1-15), gdbm, gd, postgresql-dev (>= 7.2.2-1)
Source: mirror:custom:%n-%v_src.tar.gz
CustomMirror: <<
 eur-IT: http://grass.itc.it/grass5/source/
 nam-US: ftp://grass.baylor.edu/pub/grass/grass5/source/
 eur-DE: http://www.geog.uni-hannover.de/grass/grass5/source/
<<
Source-MD5: de8d4bb462f989cc85f5c80704d2986b
SourceDirectory: %n-%v
Patch: %f.patch
PatchScript: <<
 mv Makefile.in Makefile.in.orig
 sed -e 's:GISBASE=${INST_DIR}:GISBASE=%p/share/grass5:' -e 's:\(${GISBASE}.#.\)${INST_DIR}:\1%p/share/grass5:' Makefile.in.orig > Makefile.in
<<
SetCFLAGS: -g -O2 -no-cpp-precomp
ConfigureParams: --prefix=%p/share --with-postgres-includes=%p/include/postgresql --with-readline --with-includes='%p/include /usr/X11R6/include' --bindir=%i/bin --with-dbm --with-blas --with-lapack --with-gdal --with-glw
CompileScript: (export CCACHE_DISABLE=1; ./configure %c; make)
InstallScript: <<
make install prefix=%i/share
cd %i/bin; rm gmake5 gmakelinks5
<<
DocFiles: <<
 AUTHORS BUGS ChangeLog COPYING GPL.TXT NEWS.html ONGOING README TODO.txt WARNING.html
<<
Description: GIS software
DescDetail: <<
 GRASS (Geographic Resources Analysis Support System) is a GIS(Geographical
Information System) with raster, topological vector, image processing, and
graphics production functionality that operates in the UNIX environment
through a graphical user interface and shell in X-Windows.
<<
DescUsage: <<
Just type 'grass5' at the command prompt inside an X environment.
<<
DescPort: <<
 Patchs to fix such things as removal of 'malloc.h' and to fix lots of
linking issues. Also fixed a bug in gdal and NVIZ support.
<<
